<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="turn-v">turn <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /tɜːn/    美 /tɜːrn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>转动；旋转：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>turn the tap / switch / key 
拧龙头/开关/钥匙</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The wheels of the car began to turn. 
汽车的轮子开始转动起来。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>扭转 (身体部位)；转 (身)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She turned her head in surprise. 
她惊讶地转过头来。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The children all <strong>turned to look</strong> at the famous actress as she entered the classroom.
当那个女明星走进教室时，所有孩子都转过去看她。</p><footer>2009 全国</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-vt-vi">3.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi 翻转；翻 (书页)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you <strong>turn</strong> your chairs <strong>to face</strong> this way? 
你们把椅子转过来朝这边好吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Turn</strong> ( <strong>over</strong> ) the page and look through the material.
翻过这一页，然后浏览这段材料。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-vt-vi">4.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 转弯；(使) 转向：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She waved to me as she <strong>turned the corner</strong>. 
她拐弯时向我挥了挥手。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I <strong>turned</strong> the car <strong>into</strong> the parking lot. 
我转弯把车开进了停车场。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The road turns to the left after the church. 
这条路过了教堂后向左转弯。</p></div>

<h4 id="5-vt-vi">5.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 转移：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She looked at her husband then <strong>turned her attention to</strong> the children. 
她看了看丈夫，然后把注意力转到孩子们身上。</p></div>

<h4 id="6-vt-vi">6.★ <strong>vt &amp; vi (使) 变成；(使) 变为：</strong></h4>
<ul>
<li>turn + adj:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The leaves were already turning brown. 
叶子已经变黄了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>turn sth + adj:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The shock turned her hair white. 
那次打击使她的头发变白了。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>turn + n:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He turned economist at the age of 40. 
他在40岁时成了经济学家。</p></div>

<p>注: turn表示“(使) 变成、(使) 变为”，作不及物动词时，是连系动词。  </p>
<h4 id="7vt">7.<strong>vt 到达；超过 (某一时间或年龄)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She turns 21 in June. 
她到6月就满21岁了。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It’s turned midnight. 
已经过了午夜了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="turn-around-round">turn around / round</h3>
<p>1.<strong>转身；转变；好转：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I turned around and walked out without saying a word. 
我一言未发，转身走了出去。</p><footer>外研⑥ – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>After a year’s hard work, he had turned around a badly performing department. 
经过一年的努力，他使一个业绩糟糕的部门有了起色。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-away">turn away</h3>
<p>1.<strong>把…转过去；把…打发走：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She turned her head away, feeling too ashamed to meet his gaze. 
因为害羞而不敢和他对视，她把头转了过去。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Because the hall was full, many people were turned away. 
因礼堂满了，许多人被打发走了。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-back">turn back</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(使) 往回走；改变做法：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The weather became so bad that they had to turn back. 
天气变得很糟糕,他们只好返回。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The people are <strong>turning back to</strong> natural resources to survive. 
人们又重新开始依靠自然资源生存。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-down">turn down</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>关小；调低 (音量等)：</strong><br />
反 turn up </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Could you please turn down your TV a bit? 
你可以把电视音量关小一点儿吗?</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>拒绝：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>How could you turn down such a fantastic job when you have been out of work for months?
你已经好几个月没有工作了，怎么能拒绝这么好的一份工作呢？</p><footer>2014 浙江</footer></div>

<h3 id="turn-in">turn in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>上交(BrE hand in)；上缴：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Turn in your papers, please. 
请把试卷交上来吧。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She turned in the wallet she picked up on the way.
她把在路上捡到的钱包上交了。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-into">turn into</h3>
<p>1.<strong>(使) 变成；(使) 成为：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Peter can show you how to turn an idea into an act.
彼得能教你如何把想法变成行动。</p><footer>2010 辽宁</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Newly-built wooden cottages line the street, turning the old town into a dreamland.
新建的木屋排列在街道两旁，使这座古镇变成了仙境。</p><footer>2016 北京</footer></div>

<h3 id="turn-off">turn off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>关 (水、煤气、电灯等)turn on 反 turn off：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Turn off the lights when you are not in a room. 
人不在房间时把灯关掉。</p><footer>译林⑤ – 2</footer></div>

<h3 id="turn-on">turn on</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>开 (水、煤气、电灯等)：</strong><br />
反 turn off </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He talked for several minutes, but forgot to first turn on the microphone. 
他讲了几分钟，却忘记要先把麦克风打开。</p><footer>译林⑥ – 1</footer></div>

<p>2.<strong>使 (某人) 产生兴趣：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Science fiction just doesn’t turn me on. 
科幻小说根本提不起我的兴趣。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>It was Dad who <strong>turned</strong> me <strong>on to</strong> fishing. 
是爸爸让我喜欢上钓鱼的。</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>对...发怒；突然攻击...：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He turned on his brother, who he thought, had deceived him. 
他对兄弟翻脸，认为兄弟欺骗了他。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The dogs suddenly turned on each other. 
那两条狗突然撕咬起来。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-out">turn out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>制造；生产；培养出：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The factory turns out 900 cars a week. 
这家工厂一周生产九百辆汽车。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>原来 (是)；证明 (是)；结果 (是)</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Unexpectedly the weather turned out pretty nice that day. 
出乎意料的是，那天天气特别好。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It turned out that</strong> his brother died of a heart attack.
原来他的兄弟死于心脏病。</p><footer> 2011 全国</footer></div>

<p>3.<strong>出席；参加</strong><br />
to be present in an event：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A lot of people <strong>turned out for</strong> the party.
许多人参加了聚会。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-over">turn over</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>翻身；(使) 翻转；翻过 (书页):</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He did not fall asleep, turning over in bed from time to time. 
他没睡着，在床上时不时地翻身。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t turn over the page yet. 
先别把这页翻过去。</p></div>

<p>2.<strong>移交：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He turned over the work to the secretary. 
他把工作移交给了秘书。</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>反复考虑：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She kept turning over the events of the day in her mind. 
她脑子里不断琢磨当天发生的事。</p></div>

<h3 id="turn-to">turn to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>转向；求助于：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Their talk turned to the change that had taken place in the city. 
他们的话题转到了城市发生的变化。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Please turn to the police for help when you are in trouble.  
遇到困难请向警察求助。</p><footer>2008 上海春</footer></div>

<h3 id="turn-up">turn up</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>开大；调高 (音量等)</strong><br />
反 turn down </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Turn up the radio so that I can hear the program.
把收音机音量开大些，好让我听到这个节目。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>(人) 到达；出现</strong><br />
to arrive at a place：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He promised that he would come, but he hasn’t turned up yet.
他承诺会来，但还没出现。</p><footer>2012 陕西</footer></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>(尤指失去后) 被发现：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Don’t worry about the letter — I’m sure it’ll turn up.
别为那封信担心，我相信会找到的。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Tom had to turn<strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the invitation to the party last weekend because he was too busy.  （2015 天津改）  </li>
<li>Don’t worry. I’m sure your missing glasses will turn <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ sooner or later.  （2015 湖北改）  </li>
<li>When the sports hero turned <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ at our party, he was welcomed with open arms.  （2014 安徽改）  </li>
<li>— What are you reading, Tom?
— I’m not really reading, just turning <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ the pages.   （2008 全国改）  </li>
<li>She’s having a lot of trouble with the new computer, but she doesn’t know whom to turn <strong><em>_</em></strong>_.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. down  2. up  3. up  4. over  5. to  </p></div>